SIMPLE: intermit
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intermit
<hw>In`ter*mit"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Intermitted</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Intermitting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>intermittere</ets>; <ets>inter</ets> between + <ets>mittere</ets>,
<ets>missum</ets>, to send: cf. OE. <ets>entremeten</ets> to busy (one's
self) with, F. <ets>s'entremettre</ets>. See <er>Missile</er>.]</ety>
<def>To cause to cease for a time, or at intervals; to interrupt; to
suspend.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Pray to the gods to <qex>intermit</qex> the plague.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intermit</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Intermit
<hw>In`ter*mit"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To cease for a time or at
intervals; to moderate; to be intermittent, as a fever.</def>
<rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intermittence</ent>⟦br⟧
